They thought he was hiding: The story behind the Tamil refugee believed to be Bruce McArthur’s eighth victim
To much of the world, the man in the unsettling photograph — bearded, with unkempt hair, partially shut eyes and slightly parted lips — was nameless. But as the image circulated for weeks on the news and in social media, family and friends recognized Kirushnakumar Kanagaratnam.